CF|Real Madrid]]'s youth setup in 2005, aged eight.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.es/deportes/real-madrid/abci-sueno-cumplido-sergio-reguilon-201808070129_noticia.html|title=El sue\u00f1o cumplido de Sergio Reguil\u00f3n|trans-title=The fulfilled dream of Sergio Reguil\u00f3n|publisher=[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]|language=es|date=7 August 2018|access-date=4 September 2018}}</ref> On 5 August 2015, after finishing his formation, he was loaned to [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]] side [[UD Logro\u00f1\u00e9s]] for [[2015\u201316 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|the season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rioja2.com/n-100011-401-joven_Sergio_Reguilon_llega_UD_Logrones/|title=El joven Sergio Reguil\u00f3n llega al UD Logro\u00f1\u00e9s|trans-title=The youngster Sergio Reguil\u00f3n arrives at UD Logro\u00f1\u00e9s|publisher=Rioja2|language=es|date=5 August 2015|access-date=4 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nReguil\u00f3n made his senior debut on 23 August 2015, playing the last seven minutes in a 3\u20130 home win against [[SD Compostela]]. The following 16 January, after being sparingly used, he returned to ''Los Blancos'' and was assigned to [[Real Madrid Castilla|the reserves]] also in the third division.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/real-madrid/2016/01/16/569a1b28ca4741364e8b4606.html|title=El Castilla mueve el mercado|trans-title=Castilla move the market|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=16 January 2016|access-date=4 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 August 2016, Reguil\u00f3n returned to Logro\u00f1\u00e9s also in a one-year loan deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://udlogrones.com/sergio-reguilon-cedido-por-el-madrid-castilla-hasta-final-de-temporada/|title=Sergio Reguil\u00f3n, cedido por el Madrid Castilla hasta final de temporada|trans-title=Sergio Reguil\u00f3n, loaned from Real Madrid Castilla until the end of the season|publisher=UD Logro\u00f1\u00e9s|language=es|date=23 August 2016|access-date=4 September 2018}}</ref> Now an undisputed starter, he scored eight goals during [[2016\u201317 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|the campaign]]; highlights included four past [[Bilbao Athletic]] on 2 October 2016 (5\u20133 home win).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rioja2.com/n-106752-4-reguilon-reguilon-reguilon-reguilon/|title=Reguil\u00f3n, Reguil\u00f3n, Reguil\u00f3n, Reguil\u00f3n|publisher=Rioja2|language=es|date=2 October 2016|access-date=4 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nUpon returning to Castilla, Reguil\u00f3n was a first-choice in [[Santiago Solari]]'s side, and renewed his contract on 11 May 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/real-madrid/2018/05/11/5af5ace346163f5c4e8b45b5.html|title=Reguil\u00f3n, renovaci\u00f3n 'de primer equipo'|trans-title=Reguil\u00f3n, 'first team' renewal|publisher=Marca|language=es|date=11 May 2018|access-date=4 September 2018}}</ref> On 25 August of that year, he was promoted to the main squad by manager [[Julen Lopetegui]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/real-madrid/20180825/451445104435/reguilon-madrid-lopetegui-marcelo-theo.html|title=Reguil\u00f3n se queda en el primer equipo|trans-title=Reguil\u00f3n stays in the first team|publisher=[[Mundo Deportivo]]|language=es|date=25 August 2018|access-date=4 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nReguil\u00f3n made his professional debut on 2 October 2018, starting in a 0\u20131 [[UEFA Champions League]] away loss against [[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Juventus win again as CSKA beat Madrid, Ajax hold Bayern|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2573015.html|accessdate=2 October 2018|publisher=UEFA|date=2 October 2018}}</ref> He also made his league debut on 3 November 2018, starting in a 2\u20130 [[La Liga]] home win against [[Real Valladolid]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Vinicius changes Real's luck|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2018/11/03/5bdde14422601df6698b4602.html|accessdate=3 November 2018|publisher=marca.com}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 July 2019, he was loaned to [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] for the 2019\u201320 season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sergio Reguil\u00f3n joins on loan from Real Madrid|url=https://www.sevillafc.es/en/actual/news/sergio-reguilon-joins-loan-real-madrid|accessdate=5 July 2019|publisher=sevillafc.es}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Official Announcement: Reguil\u00f3n|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2019/07/official-announcement-reguilon|accessdate=5 July 2019|publisher=realmadrid.com}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nHe was selected for the [[Spain national under-21 football team|Spain under-21 team]] for the first time by [[Luis de la Fuente Castillo]] for the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]] qualifiers against [[Romania national under-21 football team|Romania]] and [[Austria national under-21 football team|Austria]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.sefutbol.com/oficial-estos-son-internacionales-que-disputaran-amistosos-rumania-y-austria|title=De La fuente's u-21 squad for 2019 euro qualification|date=15 March 2019|accessdate=15 March 2019}}</ref> He received his first call up for the [[Spain national team|full side]] by [[Robert Moreno]] on 4 October 2019, for games against [[Norway national football team|Norway]] and [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2019/10/04/5d971507e2704e76198b4571.html|title=Reguilon, Pau Torres and Gerard Moreno named in Spain squad for first time|date=4 October 2019|website=Marca|language=en|access-date=6 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBorn in [[Madrid]], his parents are from [[Zamora (Spain)|Zamora]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.laopiniondezamora.es/deportes/2019/03/19/bonito-detalle-zamorano-reguilon-padre/1151556.html |title=El bonito detalle del zamorano Reguil\u00f3n con su padre |author=E. S. D. |date=19 March 2019 |access-date=18 May 2019 |newspaper=La Opini\u00f3n de Zamora |language=es |publisher=Prensa Ib\u00e9ria}}</ref> He is dating the [[YouTuber]] [[Marta D\u00edaz]] .<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.larazon.es/lifestyle/celebrities/marta-diaz-asi-es-el-estilo-de-la-youtuber-novia-de-reguilon-PE23278755 |title=Marta D\u00edaz, as\u00ed es el estilo de la Youtuber novia de Reguil\u00f3n |date=10 May 2019 |access-date=18 May 2019 |newspaper=[[La Raz\u00f3n (Spain)|La Raz\u00f3n]] |language=es}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|25 January 2020}}<ref>{{Soccerway|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Europe\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" valign=\"center\"|[[Real Madrid Castilla]]\n|[[2015\u201316 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2015\u201316]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]]\n|18||0||colspan=6|\u2014||18||0\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2017\u201318]]\n|30||2||colspan=6|\u2014||30||2\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!48!!2!!colspan=6|\u2014!!48!!2\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" valign=\"center\"|[[UD Logro\u00f1\u00e9s|Logro\u00f1\u00e9s]] (loan)\n|[[2015\u201316 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2015\u201316]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B\n|9||0||3||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||12||0\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2016\u201317]]\n|30||8||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||31||8\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!39!!8!!4!!0!!colspan=4|\u2014!!43!!8\n|-\n|valign=\"center\"|[[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]\n|[[2018\u201319 Real Madrid CF season|2018\u201319]]\n|[[La Liga]]\n|14||0||4||0||4||0||0||0||22||0\n|-\n|[[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] (loan)\n|[[2019\u201320 La Liga|2019-20]]\n|[[La Liga]]\n|18||1||2||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||20||1\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" |Career total\n!119!!11!!10!!0!!4!!0!!0!!0!!133!!11\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Real Madrid'''\n*[[FIFA Club World Cup]]: [[2018 FIFA Club World Cup|2018]]<ref>{{cite news|url=htt